[See also: 20120309.1065831.

The finding that SBV is "newly arrived in the Netherlands" (and the other clinically affected countries in Europe) should not be a surprise. Orthobunyavirus-related outbreaks of arthrogryposis-hydranencephaly (AG/HE) in neonate ruminants, such as those caused by the Akabane virus, are absent in endemic regions since the population undergoes seroconversion prior to the reproductive age, foeti remaining protected from infection throughout their mothers' lives. AG/HE will appear in neighbouring regions when airborne infected vectors are introduced from the endemic region, causing outbreaks of congenital malformations in susceptible, virgin populations. It will be interesting to obtain results of SBV serological investigations from other parts of Europe. - Mod.AS]

